      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STELLAR MOFEED (6) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start when she settled well back over 1200m at Caulfield Heath, beaten 6 lengths in sixth. That was in BM74 grade, though, so the drop back to 0-62 company suits and she's drawn to take up a prominent spot. DISCREET POINT (1) hasn't been far away since a maiden win three runs back, the latest effort a third over 1200m at Pakenham in Class 1 company. This is probably a touch easier than that. ISTRIANO (2) impressed when successful on debut over 1200m at Swan Hill five months ago and has not raced since. Has since been kept ticking over with a Flemington trial placing. MRS BUTT'S BOATS (3) is another who was put away after a last-start win and there's been a lot to like about the way he's performing at the jumpouts. Hard to see BILLUND (5) turning the tables on DISCREET POINT from last start, but he'll be fitter for two runs back and has drawn favourably.",
